description: Our inaugural meetup! We met each other IRL, ate cheese and crackers, talked a bit about code and of course enjoyed some good bourbon.
A special Leap Day event, we got togther to talk about time: how to manage it, when it gets away from you, and of course some round-by-zeros errors.
Round 3 moves to Gowanus, featuring an industrial backdrop and creative energy.
Phil taught us not to fear Shadow Monsters with an updated version of his world-famous Moma installtion
We learned about one coders journey to meeting the inventor of the Rubik's Cube for an interactive Google Doodle
Will AI eat all our lunch? Maybe! Let's hear from some of our members that are working closely with it. In this session we heard from ...

Have you started a new job recently, learned a new language or peice of software? How did you get started and what gave you enough motivation? At our upcoming event we'll talk about some times we tried something new and how it went
